threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered ransomware. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a sophisticated information stealer or backdoor. It employs several malicious techniques: 1) Obfuscation: It uses dynamic API resolution (sub_40182a) and a custom string decoding routine (sub_4016d5) to hide its reliance on sensitive Windows APIs. 2) Surveillance: It contains functionality to capture the user's screen (sub_404255) using GDI functions (BitBlt, CreateCompatibleBitmap) and saves the output as '.BMP' files. 3) Information Gathering: It recursively crawls the file system (sub_4067ad) and manipulates the Windows Registry to store configuration or gathered data (sub_404255, sub_404037). 4) Exfiltration: It implements a C2 communication module (sub_4031ee) that uses Base64 encoding and sends gathered data via HTTP POST requests using a characteristic format string ('%.8x=%s&%.8x=%s').
